CATEGORIES:Service
DESCRIPTION:Join our weekly Food Recovery events\, where dedicated volunte
 ers and members gather to make a difference in our community. Each week\,
  participants help collect perfectly good leftover food from Gourmet Dini
 ng and transport it to Blanton. There\, the food is repackaged into indiv
 idual microwavable containers and stocked in the food pantry\, providing 
 meals for those in need throughout the week. \nTo Participate: RSVP to at
 tend the event each week. Meet in Blanton Hall Residence Hall Kitchenette
  in the Communal Area (Tell them you are working with Food Recovery)\, Si
 gn in via Event Pass and your set!\nRequirements:\n\nVolunteers must be F
 ood Safe Certified to participate.\nComplete the certification by followi
 ng the step-by-step instructions provided in this link.\nOnce certified\,
  email your certification to foodrecoverynetwork@sgamsu.org to confirm yo
 ur eligibility to participate.\n\nYour involvement helps reduce food wast
 e and insecurity while supporting individuals in our community who are in
  need. We look forward to your participation!*Please Note: This event end
  time is dependent on the amount of food given. You can estimate for max 
 of hour and a half for recoveries.\n\nHosted by: EATS by Gourmet Dining\,
  Food Recovery Network\, Red Hawk Pantry\n\nAdditional Information can be
  found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12331651
