DESCRIPTION:The 2nd Annual STEM Summit at Montclair State University will 
 bring together students\, faculty and industry professionals from across 
 New Jersey\, to explore the interdisciplinary skills shaping the future o
 f science and mathematics. The summit will feature a keynote address and 
 include student-led research presentations across diverse scientific disc
 iplines.\n \nAttendees will participate in engaging panels\, networking o
 pportunities and interactive workshops designed to enhance key profession
 al skills. Through exploring diverse career opportunities in teaching\, a
 cademia\, industry\, and beyond\, participants will uncover how collabora
 tion across disciplines drives innovation\, problem-solving and real-worl
 d impact. \n \nThe Summit aims to foster community and amplify all studen
 t voices in STEM by empowering the next generation of scientists and inno
 vators.\n\nHosted by: College of Science and Mathematics (CSAM)\n\nAdditi
 onal Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage
 /event/12322030
DTEND:20260320T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T163251Z
DTSTART:20260320T130000Z
GEO:40.859750;-74.199750
LOCATION:Center for Environmental and Life Sciences\, Atrium
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:2nd Annual STEM Summit: Building Skills for Success
