CATEGORIES:Social
DESCRIPTION:The name Mushuk Nina means New Fire. In Andean cosmology\, fir
 e is one of the four important elements that also include air\, earth\, a
 nd water. The Mushuk Nina symbolizes the renewal of our energies\, is a K
 ichwa phrase meaning "New Year" representing the Andean New Year and a fe
 stival of renewal celebrated around the March equinox (typically March 21
 ). It symbolizes the start of a new agricultural and spiritual cycle\, fo
 cusing on purification\, community gathering\, and gratitude to Pachamama
  (Mother Earth). \nIn this event\, Kichwa community leader\, Atik Paguay\
 , and acclaimed artist Raul Ayala\, will lead an artistic and cultural ev
 ent that will bring us from learning about this celebration and its meani
 ng to participate to artistic creation led by Raul Ayala\, to the constru
 ction of the "churu" (Snail) in the ground with music and stomping ceremo
 ny.\nJoin us!\n\nHosted by: Center for Latino Heritage & Spanish Language
  Excellence\, Spanish and Latino Studies\n\nAdditional Information can be
  found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12316898
DTEND:20260323T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T163251Z
DTSTART:20260323T213000Z
GEO:40.861770;-74.199470
LOCATION:SBUS 140
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Mushuk Nina - Fuego Nuevo -Expressing the Art and Language of the 
 Andes
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12316898
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12316898
X-HOSTS:Spanish and Latino Studies
END:VEVENT
