  music 🎶 and snacks 🍿 to create a comfortable environment where student
 s can unwind while exploring a new artistic activity. Diamond art is a si
 mple and great way to spark creativity while offering a calming\, hands‑o
 n break from daily tasks.\nThis program supports student wellness by prov
 iding an easy\, enjoyable activity that anyone can complete at their own 
 pace 🌿. Students who don’t finish during the event are welcome to take t
 heir project with them to continue later. By introducing a new form of cr
 eative expression\, the program aims to encourage and promote creativity\
 , and give students a fun opportunity to relax and recharge ✨.\nLocation:
  Bloomfield Campus - Franklin Hall - Multipurpose Room (MPR - 314) Third 
 Floor\n\nHosted by: Bloomfield's Office of Residence Life\n\nAdditional I
 nformation can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event
 /12338809
