X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Social
DESCRIPTION:Step into a night of fun\, nostalgia\, and game‑show glory at 
 iParty with iCarly on Thursday\, April 9th\, from 7:00–9:00 p.m. in the S
 RC Gym. From “Are You Smarter Than a 5th Grader?” to Wheel of Fortune spi
 ns and iconic iCarly tweet‑guessing\, you’ll compete\, laugh\, and maybe 
 question your life choices. Sip from the Groovy Smoothie Station\, grab a
  donut on a stick\, jump into random dancing\, and recreate your own iCar
 ly‑style skits with props galore. It’s free\, it’s fun\, and it’s your ch
 ance to shine under the studio lights—no web show required.\nHow do I sig
 n-up?\n\nNo registration required.\nFREE for students with a valid Montcl
 air State ID.\n\nWhere and when?\n\nThursday\, April 9\, 2026\n7pm - 9pm\
 nStudent Recreation Gym\n\nPrizes:\n\nGrand Prize: J Cole Concert Tickets
 \n“Sam’s backpack” filled with random things Sam might have\nWhite Sock \
 nButter Plushie\nAlexa Speaker\nNotebook\nPens\nPoptarts\nPop up box\nBoa
 rd Game Bundle: Connect 4\, Sorry\, Uno Flip\, Taboo\, Twister\nKaraoke S
 et\nDigi Cam\n\nGames/Props:\n\nAre You Smarter Than A 5th Grader \n\n\nW
 heel of Fortune\n\n\nWho Tweeted That?” (iCarly Edition)\n\n\nRead fake o
 r real tweets from the iCarly cast\n\n\nPlayers guess who said it — Carly
 \, Sam\, Freddie\, Spencer\, or Gibby.\n\n\nAct It Out \n\n\n\nAn iCarly 
 Skit: Teams get 5–10 minutes to recreate or make up a skit like something
  from the show\n\nProps provided\nJudged on creativity and chaos\n\n\nRan
 dom dancing throughout the event with glow sticks\n\n\nProps: Old lad\, P
 olice Officer\, Clown\, Fairy\, News reporter\, King\n\n\nDecorations \nC
 ups w/ Straws\n\nBjs List\n\nFrozen fruits: Strawberries & Mango\nBananas
 \nMilk \nHoney \nYougurt \nDonuts or Donut holes \nPopcorners\nChips Flav
 or Mix\nFruit Roll Ups\nNapkins\n\nExtras:\n\nGroovy Smoothie Station: St
 rawberry Banana and Mango Flavors\nSnack Table\n\nDonuts on a stick\nRegu
 lar Snacks\n\n\n\nHosted by: Campus Recreation\n\nAdditional Information 
 can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12336898
