DESCRIPTION:As immigration policies develop\, it is best to stay educated.
  Know your rights and responsibilities!\nJoin the New Jersey Consortium f
 or Immigrant Children for a webinar on key legal and policy issues impact
 ing the Montclair community. Information will be provided on immigration 
 statuses\, policy updates\, legal protections\, judicial vs. administrati
 ve orders\, and understanding your rights if encountering law enforcement
 . Sessions are open for students\, family\, faculty\, and staff in both E
 nglish and Spanish. \nThe New Jersey Consortium for Immigrant Children (N
 JCIC) is a state-wide legal and policy advocacy and education organizatio
 n specializing in youth immigration. They provide objective legal resourc
 es\, aid\, and advice on immigration rights.\nStudent & Family English Se
 ssion: March 25\, 2:30-3:45: https://us06web.zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_
 FxYlh_kDRkCYCoOhfmEKyA#/registration\nStudent & Family Spanish Session: A
 pril 9\, 5:30-6:45: https://us06web.zoom.us/j/82724283081?pwd=KzAjQw24vxq
 mzbURBXGmbBLV3V60m3.1\n\nHosted by: College for Education and Engaged Lea
 rning\, Government Relations and Community Affairs \, Office of Student B
 elonging\, Office for Hispanic Initiatives\, Office of Community Engageme
 nt and Partnerships\, The Office for Experiential Education and Career Co
 nnections\n\nOnline Location: https://us06web.zoom.us/j/82724283081?pwd=K
 zAjQw24vxqmzbURBXGmbBLV3V60m3.1\n\nAdditional Information can be found at
 : https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12262774
