CATEGORIES:Drop By
DESCRIPTION:On view from February 3 – May 3\, 2026 in the George Segal Gal
 lery. Public hours are Tuesday – Friday\, 12 to 4 pm.\n \nAdmission is fr
 ee\, open to the public. Learn more about this exhibition\n \nCarpe Diem:
  Select Alumni in the Visual Arts is a group exhibition presented by the 
 Office for Development and Alumni Engagement and hosted by the University
  Galleries. Carpe Diem brings together twelve accomplished alumni working
  in a range of media.\n \nCurated by Sally Morgan Lehman\, who has taught
  in the Department of Art and Design at Montclair and is owner and direct
 or of Morgan Lehman Gallery in New York City\, Carpe Diem highlights the 
 breadth of artistic practices fostered at Montclair and the lasting impac
 t of its visual arts alumni.\n \nFeatured artists include Flávia Berindoa
 gue ’13\, Bisa Butler ’05\, Jonathan Calm ’97\, Kyle Coniglio ’10\, Alyss
 a Fanning ’12\, Allen Ginsberg (1943)\, Márta Kucsora (2005–06)\, Michael
  Manning ’11\, Nancy Bergman Pantirer ’80\, Tiffany Perez ’09\, William P
 ope.L ’78\, and Maria Valdivia ’24.\n \n \n\nHosted by: Alumni Engagement
 \, Montclair State University Galleries\n\nAdditional Information can be 
 found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12093971
DTEND:20260503T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260317T163251Z
DTSTART:20260203T170000Z
GEO:40.859750;-74.199740
LOCATION:George Segal Gallery\, 4th Floor of the Red Hawk Deck
